Uses of Interface
net.bytebuddy.agent.builder.AgentBuilder

  • Packages that use AgentBuilder 
    Package Description
    net.bytebuddy.agent.builder
    An agent builder is used to easily implement load-time class-transformations using a Java agent.

    • Uses of AgentBuilder in net.bytebuddy.agent.builder

      Subinterfaces of AgentBuilder in net.bytebuddy.agent.builder 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  AgentBuilder.Identified.Extendable
      This interface is used to allow for optionally providing several AgentBuilder.Transformer to applied when a matcher identifies a type to be instrumented.
      Classes in net.bytebuddy.agent.builder that implement AgentBuilder 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  AgentBuilder.Default
      The default implementation of an AgentBuilder.
      protected class  AgentBuilder.Default.Matched
      A helper class that describes a AgentBuilder.Default after supplying a AgentBuilder.RawMatcher such that one or several AgentBuilder.Transformers can be supplied.
